# Mobile Bottom Sheet for Tool Details

## Overview
Replace inline card expansion with a bottom sheet modal on mobile devices. This provides a better mobile UX by not pushing content around and giving more room for details.

## Problem with Current Approach
- Expanding a card pushes all content below it down
- User loses context of where they were in the grid
- Expanded content is cramped in card width
- Difficult to compare tools (can only expand one at a time)

## Proposed Solution
On mobile (< 768px), clicking "Show More" opens a bottom sheet that:
- Slides up from bottom
- Contains full tool details
- Has close button and swipe-to-dismiss
- Leaves card grid visible but dimmed behind

## Design Specifications

### Bottom Sheet Anatomy
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                     │
│         (Dimmed backdrop)           │
│                                     │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤  ← Drag handle
│  ═══════                            │
│  [Icon] Tool Name         [✕ Close] │
│  Full tool name • ★ 1.4K            │
├─────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                     │
│  What It Does                       │
│  [Full description text]            │
│                                     │
│  Why It's Useful                    │
│  [Full explanation]                 │
│                                     │
│  Key Features                       │
│  • Feature 1                        │
│  • Feature 2                        │
│                                     │
│  [View on GitHub →]                 │
│                                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Interaction States
- **Opening**: Slides up with spring physics
- **Open**: ~80% viewport height, scrollable content
- **Dismissing**: Swipe down past threshold or tap backdrop
- **Closed**: Slides down, backdrop fades

## Technical Implementation

### Using Framer Motion
```tsx
function ToolBottomSheet({ tool, isOpen, onClose }) {
  return (
    <AnimatePresence>
      {isOpen && (
        <>
          {/* Backdrop */}
          <motion.div
            initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
            animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
            exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
            onClick={onClose}
            className="fixed inset-0 bg-black/60 z-50"
          />

          {/* Sheet */}
          <motion.div
            initial={{ y: '100%' }}
            animate={{ y: 0 }}
            exit={{ y: '100%' }}
            transition={{ type: 'spring', damping: 25, stiffness: 300 }}
            drag="y"
            dragConstraints={{ top: 0, bottom: 0 }}
            dragElastic={0.2}
            onDragEnd={(_, info) => {
              if (info.offset.y > 100 || info.velocity.y > 500) {
                onClose();
              }
            }}
            className="fixed bottom-0 left-0 right-0 z-50 max-h-[85vh] rounded-t-3xl bg-slate-900 overflow-hidden"
          >
            {/* Drag handle */}
            <div className="sticky top-0 bg-slate-900 pt-3 pb-2">
              <div className="mx-auto h-1 w-12 rounded-full bg-slate-700" />
            </div>

            {/* Content */}
            <div className="overflow-y-auto px-6 pb-8">
              {/* Tool details here */}
            </div>
          </motion.div>
        </>
      )}
    </AnimatePresence>
  );
}
```

### Responsive Integration
```tsx
// In TldrToolCard
