# Task: GitHub Stars Fetching and Caching

## Purpose
Fetch and cache GitHub star counts for all tools to display on the /tldr page.
Stars provide social proof and should be reasonably up-to-date.

## Approach Options

### Option A: Build-Time Fetching (Recommended)
Fetch stars during build, cache in static data:
- No runtime API calls
- Fast page loads
- Stars update on each deploy
- Uses existing lib/github-stats.ts pattern

### Option B: Runtime Fetching with Cache
Fetch client-side with caching:
- Real-time star counts
- API rate limit concerns
- Additional complexity
- Loading states needed

## Implementation (Option A)

### Update build process
```typescript
// scripts/fetch-tool-stars.ts
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

const TOOL_REPOS = [
  { id: 'ntm', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/ntm' },
  { id: 'slb', repo: 'Dicklesworthstone/simultaneous_launch_button' },
  // ... all 13 tools
];

async function fetchAllStars() {
  const stars: Record<string, number> = {};

  for (const { id, repo } of TOOL_REPOS) {
    const [owner, name] = repo.split('/');
    const { data } = await octokit.repos.get({ owner, repo: name });
    stars[id] = data.stargazers_count;
    console.log(`[STARS] ${id}: ${data.stargazers_count}`);
  }

  return stars;
}

// Write to lib/data/tldr-stars.json
```

### Update tldr-data.ts
```typescript
import starsData from './data/tldr-stars.json';

export const tldrTools: TldrTool[] = [
  {
    id: 'ntm',
    stars: starsData.ntm ?? 0,
    // ...
  }
];
```

### Build script integration
```json
