# Sticky Section Navigation

## Overview
Add a sticky mini-navigation bar that shows current section and allows quick jumping between Core Tools, Supporting Tools, and other page sections.

## User Problem
- Long page requires significant scrolling
- Users lose context of where they are
- No way to quickly jump to a specific section
- Mobile especially difficult to navigate

## Design Specifications

### Desktop Implementation
- Position: Sticky at top (below main header) when scrolling past hero
- Content: "Core Tools (7)" | "Supporting Tools (6)" + progress indicator
- Active section highlighted
- Click to scroll to section

### Mobile Implementation
- Thinner bar, abbreviated labels: "Core" | "Supporting"
- Or: Dot indicators showing current position
- Swipe-able if more sections added

### Visual Design
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Core Tools (7)  •  Supporting Tools (6)  •  Setup  │
│  ═══════════════                                    │  ← Active underline
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Technical Implementation

### Intersection Observer Approach
```tsx
const sections = [
  { id: 'core-tools', label: 'Core Tools', count: coreTools.length },
  { id: 'supporting-tools', label: 'Supporting Tools', count: supportingTools.length },
];

// Track which section is in view
const [activeSection, setActiveSection] = useState(sections[0].id);

useEffect(() => {
  const observers = sections.map(section => {
    const element = document.getElementById(section.id);
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      ([entry]) => {
        if (entry.isIntersecting) {
          setActiveSection(section.id);
        }
      },
      { rootMargin: '-50% 0px -50% 0px' } // Middle of viewport
    );
    if (element) observer.observe(element);
    return observer;
  });

  return () => observers.forEach(o => o.disconnect());
}, []);
```

### Sticky Behavior
```tsx
// Show only after scrolling past hero
const heroRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
const [showNav, setShowNav] = useState(false);

useEffect(() => {
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    ([entry]) => setShowNav(!entry.isIntersecting),
    { threshold: 0 }
  );
  if (heroRef.current) observer.observe(heroRef.current);
  return () => observer.disconnect();
}, []);
```

