# Vim-Style Keyboard Navigation

## Overview
Add vim-inspired keyboard navigation to the tool grid, allowing power users to browse, expand, and interact with tools without touching the mouse.

## User Story
As a developer familiar with vim keybindings, I want to navigate the TL;DR page with j/k/h/l keys so I can explore tools efficiently without leaving the keyboard.

## Proposed Keybindings

### Navigation
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `j` / `↓` | Move to next tool |
| `k` / `↑` | Move to previous tool |
| `h` / `←` | Move left (in grid) |
| `l` / `→` | Move right (in grid) |
| `gg` | Jump to first tool |
| `G` | Jump to last tool |
| `Tab` | Standard focus navigation |

### Actions
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `Enter` / `o` | Expand/collapse focused tool |
| `O` | Expand all in current section |
| `x` | Collapse all in current section |
| `g` | Open GitHub link for focused tool |
| `c` | Copy GitHub URL to clipboard |
| `/` | Focus search bar |
| `Escape` | Clear focus / close expanded |

### Section Navigation
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `[` | Jump to Core Tools section |
| `]` | Jump to Supporting Tools section |
| `{` | Previous section |
| `}` | Next section |

## Visual Feedback
- Focused tool has visible ring (existing focus style)
- "Vim mode active" indicator (subtle, dismissible)
- Key pressed briefly shown (like Figma's key hints)

## Technical Implementation

### Focus Management
```tsx
const [focusedIndex, setFocusedIndex] = useState(-1);
const toolRefs = useRef<Map<string, HTMLElement>>(new Map());

// Register ref for each tool
const registerRef = (id: string, el: HTMLElement | null) => {
  if (el) toolRefs.current.set(id, el);
  else toolRefs.current.delete(id);
};

// Focus tool by index
const focusTool = (index: number) => {
  const tools = [...coreTools, ...supportingTools];
  const tool = tools[index];
  if (tool) {
    toolRefs.current.get(tool.id)?.focus();
    setFocusedIndex(index);
  }
};
```

### Keyboard Handler
```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  const handleKeyDown = (e: KeyboardEvent) => {
    // Skip if in input/textarea
    if (['INPUT', 'TEXTAREA'].includes(document.activeElement?.tagName ?? '')) {
      return;
    }

    const allTools = [...coreTools, ...supportingTools];
    const cols = 3; // Grid columns

    switch (e.key) {
      case 'j':
      case 'ArrowDown':
        e.preventDefault();
        focusTool(Math.min(focusedIndex + cols, allTools.length - 1));
        break;
      case 'k':
      case 'ArrowUp':
        e.preventDefault();
        focusTool(Math.max(focusedIndex - cols, 0));
        break;
      case 'h':
      case 'ArrowLeft':
        e.preventDefault();
        focusTool(Math.max(focusedIndex - 1, 0));
        break;
      case 'l':
      case 'ArrowRight':
        e.preventDefault();
        focusTool(Math.min(focusedIndex + 1, allTools.length - 1));
        break;
      case 'Enter':
      case 'o':
        e.preventDefault();
        toggleExpand(allTools[focusedIndex]?.id);
        break;
      case 'g':
        if (e.shiftKey) { // G = last
          e.preventDefault();
          focusTool(allTools.length - 1);
        } else {
          // Open GitHub
          window.open(allTools[focusedIndex]?.href, '_blank');
        }
        break;
      case '/':
        e.preventDefault();
        searchRef.current?.focus();
        break;
      case 'Escape':
        e.preventDefault();
        setFocusedIndex(-1);
        document.activeElement?.blur();
        break;
    }
  };

  window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
  return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKeyDown);
}, [focusedIndex, coreTools, supportingTools]);
```

### gg Detection (Double Key)
```tsx
const lastKey = useRef<{ key: string; time: number } | null>(null);

// In handler
if (e.key === 'g') {
  const now = Date.now();
  if (lastKey.current?.key === 'g' && now - lastKey.current.time < 500) {
    // gg detected - go to first
    focusTool(0);
    lastKey.current = null;
  } else {
    lastKey.current = { key: 'g', time: now };
  }
}
```

