# Spring Physics for Card Expand/Collapse

## Overview
Replace the current basic height animation with spring-based physics for a more natural, premium feel when expanding and collapsing tool cards.

## Current State
- `tldr-tool-card.tsx` lines 285-290
- Uses `{ height: 'auto', opacity: 1 }` with basic `duration: 0.3`
- Feels mechanical and lacks life
- Content appears all at once

## Proposed Animation

### Spring Parameters
```tsx
// Natural, bouncy feel without being cartoonish
const springConfig = {
  type: 'spring',
  stiffness: 300,  // Quick but not snappy
  damping: 25,     // Some bounce but settles fast
  mass: 0.8,       // Lightweight feel
};
```

### Expand Choreography
```
T+0ms:    Container height begins expanding (spring)
T+50ms:   "Why It's Useful" section fades in
T+100ms:  "Key Features" section fades in
T+150ms:  "Implementation Highlights" fades in
T+200ms:  "Tech Stack" fades in
T+250ms:  "Synergies" section fades in
T+300ms:  "Use Cases" fades in
```

### Collapse (Reverse)
- Content fades out all at once (faster)
- Then height collapses with spring

## Technical Implementation

### Container Animation
```tsx
<motion.div
  initial={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
  animate={{ height: 'auto', opacity: 1 }}
  exit={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
  transition={{
    height: {
      type: 'spring',
      stiffness: 300,
      damping: 25,
    },
    opacity: { duration: 0.2 }
  }}
>
```

### Staggered Content
```tsx
const contentVariants = {
  hidden: { opacity: 0, y: 10 },
  visible: (i: number) => ({
    opacity: 1,
    y: 0,
    transition: {
      delay: i * 0.05,
      duration: 0.3,
    }
  }),
};

// In render
{sections.map((section, i) => (
  <motion.div
    key={section.title}
    custom={i}
    variants={contentVariants}
    initial="hidden"
    animate={isExpanded ? "visible" : "hidden"}
  >
    {section.content}
  </motion.div>
))}
```

### Using AnimatePresence Properly
```tsx
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
  {isExpanded && (
    <motion.div
      key="expanded-content"
      initial={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
      animate={{ height: 'auto', opacity: 1 }}
      exit={{ height: 0, opacity: 0 }}
      transition={{
        height: { type: 'spring', stiffness: 300, damping: 25 },
        opacity: { duration: 0.15 }
      }}
    >
      <motion.div
        initial={{ opacity: 0 }}
        animate={{ opacity: 1 }}
        transition={{ delay: 0.1, duration: 0.2 }}
      >
        {/* Content with stagger */}
      </motion.div>
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

## Files to Modify
- `components/tldr-tool-card.tsx` - Lines 283-394

## Before/After Comparison
| Aspect | Before | After |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Height change | Linear 0.3s | Spring (bouncy settle) |
| Content reveal | All at once | Staggered sections |
| Collapse | Same as expand | Faster, content first |
| Feel | Mechanical | Natural, premium |

## Reduced Motion
- Instant expand/collapse (no animation)
- Content still staggers but instantly (opacity only)
- No spring bounce

## Performance Notes
- `layout` prop can cause expensive recalculations
- Test with multiple cards expanded
- Use `layoutId` only if necessary

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Expand uses spring physics for height
- [ ] Content sections stagger in on expand
- [ ] Collapse is faster than expand
- [ ] Animation feels natural, not cartoonish
- [ ] No layout shift or jank
- [ ] Works with multiple cards expanded
- [ ] Respects reduced motion (instant)
- [ ] Maintains proper focus management

